                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d772">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2829: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gunther</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-11-17T13:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 17, 1922—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>229. Department’s 157, October 27, 4 p.m.<note n="17" xml:id="d772fn17">See
                        footnote 15, <ref target="#pg_927">p. 927</ref>.</note> Foreign Office
                    states under date of October [<hi rend="italic">November</hi>] 15th that,
                    confirming the declaration transmitted in the Embassy’s number 203, October 24,
                    10 p.m., the Italian Government adheres to the program of action proposed by the
                    Government of the United States and has already instructed its Minister at
                    Peking to act accordingly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gunther</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
